%N A395600 Decimal expansion of the expected area of the triangular part formed by intersecting a unit-area equilateral triangle with a random line whose direction and perpendicular distance from the origin are independently and uniformly selected at random, given that the line intersects the triangle.
%C A395600 The probability that the line will pass through a vertex, and thus will partition the triangle into two triangular parts, is 0.
%H A395600 Emanuel Czuber, <a href="https://archive.org/details/geometwahrschein00czubrich/page/n233/mode/1up">Geometrische Wahrscheinlichkeiten und Mittelwerte</a>, B. G. Teubner, Leipzig, 1884, pp. 222-223.
%H A395600 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395600 Equals (3*log(3) - 2)/6 = log(3)/2 - 1/3.
%e A395600 0.215972811000721512364289285127929518990411945578041...
%t A395600 RealDigits[(3*Log[3] - 2)/6, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395600 (PARI) (3*log(3) - 2)/6
